OL,3,CWordsworth Grasmere launches daffodil
OL,4,Ctrail to celebrate famous poem
OL,6,FWordsworth Grasmere has launched its
OL,7,Fdaffodil trail, celebrating the spring
OL,8,Fflowers which inspired one of the
OL,9,Fpoet's most famous works.
OL,11,FThe Romantic poet, born in
OL,12,FCockermouth, wrote 'I wandered lonely
OL,13,Fas a Cloud' in his Grasmere home Dove
OL,14,FCottage, where the trail begins.
OL,16,FThe lyric poem was inspired by a
OL,17,Fcollection of daffodils Wordsworth
OL,18,Fencountered during a walk with his
OL,19,Fyounger sister Dorothy in 1802.
